README

I'm running windows - wsl
I wrote in python

Commands I ran:
1. source venv/bin/activate
2. pip install numpy opencv-python
3. python particlefilter.py

Opencv and numpy are required to run my Particle Filter simulation.
Currently running the script allows for pressing any key or 'enter' to
move the simulation to the next time step.

The current file that is tested is 'BayMap.png'. To change this edit
line 205 in particlefilter.py to use another map / image.
Line 205:
    parser.add_argument('--map',        default='BayMap.png')

I also ran the simulation on images not included in the hw spec.


1. python evaluate.py

This is what I used to perform and generate my tables for my 
experiments.